article.headline: Colgate 64, Lehigh 60
article.story: HAMILTON, N.Y. -- Murphy Burnatowski scored 19 points and Pat Moore had 17, and Colgate bolted to a 22-4 lead and held on to upset Lehigh 64-60 in Patriot League play Saturday afternoon. The Raiders (10-17, 4-6), who snapped a three-game losing streak, led 38-16 with 4:04 left in the half. Gabe Knutson and Anthony D'Orazio scored 17 points apiece and Holden Greiner had 12 for the Mountain Hawks (18-6, 8-2), whose four-game winning streak was halted. Lehigh was tied with Bucknell atop the Patriot League at 8-1, but Bucknell also lost, falling to Lafayette 63-62. Colgate shot 38.1 percent on 3-pointers (8 of 21) to Lehigh's 16.7 percent (3 of 18), beat the Mountaineers on the boards 40-33, and the Raiders' bench outscored Lehigh's 15-2. Lehigh tied Colgate at 56-all on a 3-pointer by D'Orazio with 3:04 left, but James Brandon made two free throws at 1:53, and Lehigh never caught up.
